{"kind":"finding_approved","payload":{"confidence":"HYPOTHESIS","finding":{"analyst_note":"A service named 'spoolfool' with a shell image is the public signature of the SpoolFool exploit (CVE-2022-21999), which abuses the Print Spooler's SpoolDirectory handling to drop a DLL and execute as SYSTEM. The service is the persistence / payload-delivery artifact, not the exploit primitive.","artifact_offset":null,"artifact_path":"/home/assessor/Desktop/PUG-Projects/sans-hackathon/evidence/attack-samples/LM_Remote_Service02_7045.evtx","case_id":"dir-70ca157294e2094d","confidence":"HYPOTHESIS","cves":["CVE-2022-21999"],"derived_from":null,"description":"hypothesis: EVTX EID 7045 records installation of service 'spoolfool' (image cmd.exe) (record 1); service installation is a durable persistence and lateral-movement mechanism \u2014 the image path looks suspicious; corroborate the binary and origin before response.","event_id":"9ae50879-7a4f-4731-a6f0-3579ff68f402","event_type":"Finding","finding_id":"f-B-evtx-service-install","host":"WIN-77LTAPHIQ1R.example.corp","mitre_technique":"T1543.003","named_technique":"SpoolFool \u2014 Windows Print Spooler privilege escalation","next_pivot":"Pull the Spooler driver directory (C:\\Windows\\System32\\spool\\drivers), the spoolsv.exe child-process tree, and System EIDs 7045/7000/7009 around this time; hash the service image and check Amcache/Prefetch for execution.","pool_origin":"B","prior_observations":[],"replay_actual_sha256":"c02ce481d2f1a84b7657d60c0e7c308f17209bbd2c6f2bdfe473345353942df5","replay_artifact":{"actual_sha256":"c02ce481d2f1a84b7657d60c0e7c308f17209bbd2c6f2bdfe473345353942df5","arguments_sha256":"72f1c5c713ca282f262a3f930b42d522e3ad50e80d65b6d37de891c34c1a98a3","drift_class":"exact_match","drift_reason":"replay output_sha256 matches audit log","error":null,"expected_sha256":"c02ce481d2f1a84b7657d60c0e7c308f17209bbd2c6f2bdfe473345353942df5","matched":true,"replay_tool_call_id":"b0659ab2-6d01-4443-aebd-64ec495a740f","